description:
Rune Balot is a prostitute who is nearly murdered by Ciel, an enigmatic casino manager, who suffers from a disease that forces him to remove and store his memories. A professor brings Rune back to life as a cyborg with the ability to control electronics and partners her up with a selfaware universal tool named Oeufcocque. Together they begin to unravel the mystery behind Ciel and Rune sheds the role of the victim, but must struggle between seeking justice and vengeance.

description:
Rune Balot is a prostitute who is nearly murdered by Ciel, an enigmatic casino manager, who suffers from a disease that forces him to remove and store his memories. A victim for most of her life, Rune faces a choice. While on the brink of death, she is given the opportunity to live. It is not a simple choice for a victim, but Rune takes it. A professor brings Rune back to life as a cyborg with the ability to control electronics and partners her up with a self-aware universal tool named Oeufcocque. description: Casanova Quinn is a secret secret agent, and a pawn in a game of espionage-chess played by his father Cornelius and the forces of E.M.P.I.R.E. against alllll the bad guys in the whole wide world. When a mission goes haywire and Casanova disappears, all hell breaks loose across the span of the space-time continuum itself. As archrival Newman Xeno conspires to break both the laws of man and physics, the fabric of all-that-is begins to fray. Clearing the way for that delightful little Armageddon is Casanova's twin sister, Zephyr, killing her way through a blood-soaked hit list that ends with their father. All this as a super-vixen from the future scrambles to unravel the mystery at the heart of it all: WHEN IS CASANOVA QUINN? The sex is sexier and the violence is violent-ier in this, the second breathtaking volume of CASANOVA, the comic that Entertainment Weekly calls "Sexy... gripping and darkly funny." Collecting CASANOVA: GULA #1-4.
name: TPB

description: Meet Casanova Quinn: prodigal son of a law-and-order family hell-bent on keeping the world safe and sound, now blackmailed into betraying his father and the international law enforcement organization he controls. LUXURIA collects the first volume of CASANOVA as its titular star transforms from devil-may-care thrill-seeker into the most dangerous man in the world. What happens when the ultimate player gets played? Find out in this genre-bending sci-spy epic. Gorgeously re-colored and re-lettered by hand, this staggering psychedelic spy-fi epic is collected for the first time as it was meant to be made. By the Eisner award-winning team of Matt Fraction (INVINCIBLE IRON MAN, THOR, UNCANNY X-MEN), Gabriel Bá (UMBRELLA ACADEMY, BPRD: 1947), and Fábio Moon (DAYTRIPPER, SUGARSHOCK). With all-new, all-different, never-before-seen bonus material!
name: Vol. 1

description: Published by World Distributors as a tie-in to the Doctor Who spin-off K-9 and Company, featuring K-9 and Sarah Jane Smith investigating various mysteries. Since the K-9 and Company pilot, which ultimately proved to be the only episode produced, had pitted the Doctor's two friends against a menace with a supernatural cover, the stories in the annual followed suit.
First of three Dylan issues, this covers Dylan in the 60's as he takes over the folk-rock legacy of Woody Guthrie.
name: Bob Dylan, Part One: Kingdom Come (1941-1965)

description:
Watanuki's vow to the witch Yûko, who has disappeared, leaves him in charge of the shop where wishes must be granted to those who meet the price. Enter a deranged customer who is determined to capture the heart of the man she is stalking. Now Watanuki may have no choice but to deliver his friend Shizuka Dômeki into the arms of this unstable woman!

Originally published in Japanese. English translation by William Flanagan.
name: Vol. 18

description:
Kimihiro Watanuki has passed through many trials by fire. Once an indentured servant, he has matured and become the poised and skilled keeper of the shop that grants wishes. But Watanuki's final wish is for himself: to meet Yuko one more time. With Yuko long vanished from our world, is it even possible? That question and others are answered now in the concluding volume of the bestselling manga xxxHOLiC!

Originally published in Japanese. English translation written by William Flanagan.
name: Vol. 19

description: The first Doctor Who-related comic tie-in, starring his foes the Daleks, published by Souvenir Press in June 1964. Notable not only for being the first adventures of the Daleks without the Doctor, but also for including the first print adventure of the Doctor's granddaughter Susan.
The second Souvenir Press volume starring the Daleks, notable for including a story pitting them against the Mechonoids, robots that had featured in the Doctor Who TV serial "The Chase."
name: The Dalek World

description: The third and final Dalek book from Souvenir Press, which included the comic strip debut of the Doctor's travelling companion Sara Kingdom, whom Dalek creator Terry Nation intended to spin off as the star of a new Dalek TV show which he hoped to sell to a US network. Ultimately the concept failed to sell, and the Daleks would return to menace the Doctor both on TV and in the comics. It would be nearly a decade before the Daleks again ventured into solo Annuals action, with the release of World Distributors' Dalek Annuals.
name: The Dalek Outer Space Book

description: The second Doctor Who Holiday Special, published by Polystyle, who held the Doctor Who comic strip license at the time. The contents included articles, quizzes, crosswords and pin-ups from the TV show, as well as three new comic strips, Doomcloud, Perils in Paris and Who's Who, the first of which was the debut of TV companion Sarah Jane Smith in the comics, plus a reprint of part of the Dalek Chronicles, Power Play, which had originally appeared in TV21.
name: Doctor Who Holiday Special

description: The first Doctor Who Holiday Special, published by Polystyle, who held the Doctor Who comic strip license at the time. The contents included articles, quizzes, crosswords and pin-ups from the TV show, as well as a reprinted comic strips originally published in TV21 as part of the Dalek Chronicles (Dalek Dual), plus new strips Fogbound and Secret of the Tower and text story Smash Hit.
name: Doctor Who Holiday Special

description: The third Polystyle Doctor Who special, released three years after the last Doctor Who Holiday Special. Like its predecessors it included articles, comic strips and a text story, but unlike the previous issues the comic strips were not strictly speaking new. Instead it used reprints of past stories from TV Action, with artwork modified to replace Jon Pertwee's third Doctor with Tom Baker's fourth. Only the text story was completely new. It would be Polystyle's last Doctor Who Special before losing the license to Marvel UK.

description: England, 1940… London is under a hail of bombs, but while the civilian population is being decimated by the Third Reich’s attack from the air, another war is being fought out in the corridors of power. Among the high-ranking figures, not all of them are enemies of Germany. Lord De Vere and other conspirators, in agreement with some exponents of MI6, Her Majesty’s Secret Service, are urging that a separate peace be signed. Fortunately, Prime Minister Churchill has organized an alternative espionage network, headed by Major Foster, and this network can also count on the presence of Godwin Brumowski, the former Polish aviator in the Great War, who subsequently became a vampire in the service of Draka. Sixty years on, the unfolding events in the De Vere family get intertwined with those of the “Lupi Azzurri” sect, which means the clash with Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak will be inevitable…
name: Il castello di Barbablù

description: Dampyr, Tesla and Kurjak once again have to confront one of their most dreaded adversaries: the terror multinational known as Temsek, probably governed by a Master of the Night. Under the leaden skies of Sheffield, a city that hosts mysterious crimes, they encounter an unexpected ally: journalist Jeff Carter, a man who knows more than he would have you believe…
name: I delitti di Sheffield

description: Araxe, the vampire lover of the anarchic poet, Victor, reawakened from her century-long sleep. There is a nest of nightmares in Paris underworld, a road to hell that rouses everybody’s worst fears. It is not a hard road to take: buying a subway ticket, for the Line 4, you could get out at a non-existant station, where you’ll meet death or madness What will Harlan Draka find there?
name: I sotterranei di Parigi

description: Herla, Herlenkönig, Hellequin and, to finish it up, Alichino or Arlecchino… These are just some of the many names which, ever since medieval times, have designated the King of the Dead, the condottiero of a ghastly army that periodically emerges from the nether world to bring devastation and terror on earth. The scene now is the wild land of Brittany, where Harlan, as well as Tesla and Kurjak who go with him, arrives in search of the terrifying "Horde of Hellequin”… Who is Hellequin? What did he have to do with the past of Araxe, in the era of the French Revolution? Is it true that his army of dead warriors was engaged in a clash with the ruthless General Westermann's "infernal column", the one that was responsible for the massacres in Brittany and Vandea? And whose bell still tolls in the ruined abbey of Kergelen? ... As she recounts her long and tragic tale, beautiful Araxe will gradually unravel many of these queries, which arose at the time she was known, by Republicans and Chouans, as the Baroness of Kerkadio...
name: La colonna infernale

description: For Monsieur Saugrènes, finding an extremely rare copy of “Nikolaus’s tales” has truly been a most pleasant surprise, but as often happens in this world, it turns out to be rather short-lived and deceptive. For alas, there is someone who delights in transforming the fantasies of the sulphureous author into reality, concocting a game that soon proves to be far from innocent. Mysterious cafés, sinister houses, grotesque wax images packed into museums appear unexpectedly, only to disappear just as unpredictably, although not before whisking away some unlucky guy with them. And when even Saugrènes vanishes into thin air, Caleb makes arrangements for Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak to intervene…
name: Il Dottor Cinderella
Frank Zappa
Kate Bush

description: Seeking revenge for the death of a friend, 8-Opus and Daedalus must face the combined might of the very same enemy that killed their powerful ally. Hiding their identities, the two demigods march among a rebel battalion and lay siege to Castle Stonefang, a fortress bristling with god-killing weaponry.

description:
First volume of the Doctor Who Storybook, Panini's replacement for the Doctor Who Annual after the BBC took the license to produce annuals back in-house following the success of Panini's 2006 annual. While the new BBC annual concentrated more on features, and had minimal story content, the Storybook consisted completely of new stories, as its name suggests, a mixture of illustrated prose shorts and comic strips, most written by established Doctor Who fiction veterans, including several writers working on the TV series, including future series head writer/producer Steven Moffat.

Contents included:

Opera of Doom! (comic strip)

Cuckoo Spit (text story)

The Cat Came Back (text story)

Once Upon a Time (text story)

Gravestone House (text story)

Untitled (text story)

No One Died (text story)

Corner of the Eye (text story)

description: When ITV bought the rights to air Sherlock Holmes and Doctor Watson, a Polish/American joint venture based on Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's Sherlock Holmes that starred Geoffrey Whitehead as the eponymous detective and Donald Pickering as Doctor Watson, Grandreams bought a license to produce a TV tie-in annual for the UK market. Unfortunately ITV's plans to air the series, which included adaptations of existing Holmes tales alongside brand new stories, fell through, so the show never aired in the UK, but Grandreams released their annual anyway. Unsurprisingly, no subsequent annuals were forthcoming.
